        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-07-12T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-07-12T08:00:00-05:00" n="448"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d448">
                <head>448. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Embassy in Egypt</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d448fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 123–<persName corresp="#p_BHA1">Byroade, Henry A.</persName> Secret;
                        Eyes Only. Received at 3:58 a.m., July 13.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1956-07-12T15:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 12, 1956—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>61. For Secretary. I felt it best to tell <persName corresp="#p_NNNCGA1"
                        >Nasser</persName> directly of my recall,<note n="2" xml:id="d448fn2">See
                            <ref target="#d414">Document 414</ref>.</note> which could not be
                    arranged until last evening. I later on delivered formal papers to <persName
                        corresp="#p_FM1">Fawzi</persName>. I told <persName corresp="#p_FM1"
                        >Fawzi</persName> of our timing problem due to Senate<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d448fn3">
                        <persName corresp="#p_BHA1">Byroade</persName>’s successor, <persName
                            corresp="#p_HRA1">Raymond A. Hare</persName>, was commissioned August 14
                        during a recess of the Senate. <persName corresp="#p_HRA1">Hare</persName>
                        presented his credentials on September 25, 15 days after <persName
                            corresp="#p_BHA1">Byroade</persName>’s departure.</note> and he promised
                    to do his best to leave instructions that we receive written agreement during
                    their absence. He told me just now at airport that he had been unable do this as
                    their pre-departure schedule was just too crowded. Am sending you my personal
                    letter summary of last night’s discussions.<note n="4" xml:id="d448fn4">Not
                        printed. (Department of State, Central Files, 123–<persName
                            corresp="#p_BHA1">Byroade, Henry A.</persName>)</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BHA1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Byroade</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
